        <main class="main" id="main" tabindex="-1">
            <div class="container">

                
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-12">

                            <!-- Must reside outside the <h1> tag, as divs are not allowed in <h1>'s -->
                            <h1 class="or-page-title">
                                
	
	

                                OHA Public Civil Rights
                            </h1>
                            <div class="form-group or-show-if-side-navigation">
                                <button class="btn btn-default btn-block hidden-md hidden-lg hidden-xl" type="button" data-toggle="offcanvas" data-target="#OregonSideNavigation" data-canvas="body"><span class="fa fa-bars notranslate" aria-hidden="true"></span> <span>Site Navigation</span></button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    

                    

                        <div class="row">

                        <div class="col-md-3">
                            <!-- side navigation publishing data source -->
                            

                            <!-- side navigation menu -->
                            <nav id="OregonSideNavigation" aria-label="Site Navigation" class="or-side-navigation navmenu navmenu-default navmenu-fixed-left offcanvas-sm">
	<ul class="nav">
		<li class=""><a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/EI/Pages/index.aspx">E&amp;I Home</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Contact-Us.aspx">Contact Us</a></li><li class=""><a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/EI/Pages/Behavioral-Health-Equity-Program.aspx">Behavioral Health Equity</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/CCCE.aspx">Cultural Competence Continuing Education</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Reports.aspx">Data and Reports</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/DELTA.aspx">Developing Equity Leadership through Training and Action (DELTA)</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Committees.aspx">Committees and Councils</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Policies.aspx">Policies and Procedures</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Demographics.aspx">REALD and SOGI</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/RHEC.aspx">Regional Health Equity Coalitions</a></li><li class=""><a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/EI/Pages/Rulemaking.aspx">Rulemaking</a></li><li class=""><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/OEI-Training-Opportunities.aspx">Training, Resources, and Technical Assistance</a></li>
	</ul>
</nav>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-9" >

                    

                    
	
	

                    <!--Sharepoint's placeholder-->

                    
	
	
	
	
	
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField1__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><p>
   <br>
   <br>
</p><p>This page is about the Oregon Health Authority's Nondiscrimination Policy for the Public.&#160; If you are an OHA employee, OHA board or commission member, OHA volunteer, OHA intern, or an OHA prospective employee please visit the 
   <a href="/oha/EI/Pages/Employee-Rights.aspx">Employee Rights Page.</a></p><p class="lead">The Oregon Health Authority (OHA) complies with state and federal civil rights laws and does not discriminate on the basis of&#58;<br></p><p></p><ul><li>Age</li><li>Color<br></li><li>Disability<br></li><li>Gender identity</li><li>Language</li><li>Marital Status</li><li>National Origin</li><li>Pregnancy<br></li><li>Race<br></li><li>Religion<br></li><li>Sex</li><li>Sexual Orientation</li></ul><p></p><h2 class="ews-h2-gray-stripe">Do you think OHA has discriminated against you?</h2><p>Please report your concern by filling out one of our complaint forms located below. OHA will make reasonable modifications for people with disabilities and people with limited English to make sure you have full access to the complaint filing and investigation process.&#160;If you are not able to submit a written complaint or if you need a modification please contact the Civil Rights Coordinator by calling 844-882-7889. Please leave a detailed voicemail message. All relay calls are accepted.&#160;Claims of intimidation or retaliation related to the complaint process will be handled promptly and in the same manner as a claim of discrimination.<br></p><div class="ms-rtestate-read ms-rte-wpbox"><div class="ms-rtestate-notify  ms-rtestate-read efd89f9a-cdb9-4b13-b1ce-db5163d2bba7" id="div_efd89f9a-cdb9-4b13-b1ce-db5163d2bba7" unselectable="on"><div id="MSOZoneCell_WebPartWPQ1" class="s4-wpcell-plain ms-webpartzone-cell ms-webpart-cell-vertical ms-fullWidth ">
	<div class="ms-webpart-chrome ms-webpart-chrome-vertical ms-webpart-chrome-fullWidth ">
	<div    id="WebPartWPQ1"  class="ms-WPBody noindex "   style="" ><div id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl40_g_efd89f9a_cdb9_4b13_b1ce_db5163d2bba7">
		<div class="or-taskbox card panel panel-default">
			<h3 class="card-title text-xs-center text-center or-taskbox-title">
				OHA Report of Discrimination
			</h3><ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
				<li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/EI/Documents/OHA%20Report%20of%20Discrimination%20-%20Simplified%20Chinese.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination - Simplified Chinese</a></li><li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://apps.state.or.us/Forms/Served/lr2997.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination – Russian</a></li><li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://apps.state.or.us/Forms/Served/li2997.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination – Somali</a></li><li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://apps.state.or.us/Forms/Served/le2997.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination – English</a></li><li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://apps.state.or.us/Forms/Served/ls2997.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination – Spanish</a></li><li class="list-group-item"><a href="https://apps.state.or.us/Forms/Served/lv2997.pdf">OHA Report of Discrimination – Vietnamese</a></li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div><div class="ms-clear"></div></div>
</div>
</div></div><div id="vid_efd89f9a-cdb9-4b13-b1ce-db5163d2bba7" unselectable="on" style="display&#58;none;"></div></div><h3>Mail, email or fax&#160;the completed form to&#58;<br></h3><p>
   <strong></strong></p><blockquote class="ms-rteElement-BlockQuote">
   <strong>Equity and Inclusion Division</strong><br>Attn&#58;&#160;Mavel Morales<br>Civil Rights Coordinator<br>421 SW Oak Street, Suite 750<br>Portland OR 97204<br></blockquote><div><blockquote class="ms-rteElement-BlockQuote">Phone&#58; 971-673-3420<br>Fax&#58; 971-673-1330<br>Email&#58;&#160;<a href="mailto&#58;oha.publiccivilrights@odhsoha.oregon.gov">oha.publiccivilrights@odhsoha.oregon.gov</a><br></blockquote><h3 style="font-family&#58;&quot;helvetica neue&quot;, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">How to file complaints&#58;<br></h3><div class="ms-rtestate-read ms-rte-embedcode ms-rte-embedil ms-rtestate-notify" unselectable="on"> 
      <iframe width="500" height="315" src="https&#58;//www.youtube.com/embed/7_rSi48NUco" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0"></iframe>&#160;</div></div><div><h2 class="ews-h2-gray-stripe">Relevant Policies&#160;and Procedures</h2><ul><li> 
         <a href="https&#58;//secure.sos.state.or.us/oard/displayDivisionRules.action?selectedDivision=4200" target="_blank">Oregon Administrative Rules - Nondiscrimination policy and procedures</a></li><li> 
         <a href="/oha/EI/Pages/ADA-Notice.aspx" target="_blank">Notice under the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</a><br></li><li><a href="/oha/EI/Pages/OHA-Language-Access-and-Nondiscrimination-Policies-for-the-Public.aspx"><span data-teams="true">OHA Language Access and Nondiscrimination Policies for the Public</span></a><br></li><li>
         <a href="https&#58;//sharedsystems.dhsoha.state.or.us/DHSForms/Served/dhsoha010-013.pdf" target="_blank">Auxiliary Aids, Alternate Formats&#160;and Language Access Services Policy (AAAFLAS)</a><br></li></ul><h3>Nondiscrimination policy complies with all state and federal laws including&#58;<br></h3><ul><li> 
         <a href="http&#58;//www.justice.gov/crt/about/cor/coord/titlevi.php" target="_blank">Title VI of the Civil Rights Act of 1964</a></li><li> 
         <a href="http&#58;//www.ada.gov/pubs/adastatute08.htm" target="_blank">Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990 (as amended)</a></li><li> 
         <a href="https&#58;//www.dol.gov/agencies/oasam/centers-offices/civil-rights-center/statutes/section-504-rehabilitation-act-of-1973" target="_blank">Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973</a></li><li> 
         <a href="https&#58;//www.oregonlegislature.gov/bills_laws/ors/ors659A.html" target="_blank">Oregon Revised Statute Chapter 659A</a></li><li> 
         <a href="https&#58;//www.federalregister.gov/documents/2024/05/06/2024-08711/nondiscrimination-in-health-programs-and-activities" target="_blank">Section 1557 of the Affordable Care Act</a><br></li></ul><h2 class="ews-h2-gray-stripe">You may also have the right to file a&#160;complaint with&#58;</h2><h3>Within 180 days of the Alleged Discrimination&#58;<br></h3><p> 
      <a href="http&#58;//www.justice.gov/crt/complaint/" target="_blank">US Department of Justice</a><br> Civil Rights Division<br> 950 Pennsylvania Avenue, N.W.<br> Washington, D.C. 20530<br><span data-teams="true"><a rel="noreferrer noopener" title="tel&#58;1-855-856-1247" target="_blank">1-855-856-1247</a> (toll-free)&#160;<span data-teams="true">(TTY) <a rel="noreferrer noopener" title="tel&#58;202-514-0716" target="_blank">(202) 514-0716</a></span></span><br></p><p>
      <br>
   </p><p> 
      <a href="https&#58;//www.hhs.gov/civil-rights/filing-a-complaint/complaint-process/index.html" target="_blank">US Health and Human Services Office of Civil Rights</a><br><span data-teams="true">Centralized Case Management Operations<br>
U.S. Department of Health and Human Services<br>
200 Independence Avenue, S.W.<br>
Room 509F HHH Bldg.<br>
Washington, D.C. 20201</span><br></p><p>Customer Response Center&#58; (800) 368-1019<br> Fax&#58; 202- 619-3818<br> TDD&#58; 1-800-537-7697<br> Email&#58;&#160;<a href="mailto&#58;OCRComplaint@hhs.gov">OCRComplaint@hhs.gov</a>&#160;<br></p><p>
      <br>
   </p><h3>Within&#160;One Year of Alleged Discrimination&#58;<br></h3><p> 
      <a href="/boli/civil-rights/pages/default.aspx" target="_blank" data-or-analytics-event-attached="true">Oregon Bureau of Labor and Industries (BOLI)</a><br>1800 SW 1st Ave, Suite 500</p><span data-teams="true"><p>
  Portland, OR 97201</p><ul><li>Email&#58; <a aria-label="Link   BOLI_help@boli.oregon.gov" href="mailto&#58;BOLI_help@boli.oregon.gov" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="fui-Link ___1q1shib f2hkw1w f3rmtva f1ewtqcl fyind8e f1k6fduh f1w7gpdv fk6fouc fjoy568 figsok6 f1s184ao f1mk8lai fnbmjn9 f1o700av f13mvf36 f1cmlufx f9n3di6 f1ids18y f1tx3yz7 f1deo86v f1eh06m1 f1iescvh fhgqx19 f1olyrje f1p93eir f1nev41a f1h8hb77 f1lqvz6u f10aw75t fsle3fq f17ae5zn" title="mailto&#58;boli_help@boli.oregon.gov">BOLI_help@boli.oregon.gov</a></li><li><a rel="noreferrer noopener" title="tel&#58;+19712453844" target="_blank">971-245-3844</a></li><li><a rel="noreferrer noopener" title="tel&#58;+711" target="_blank">TTY Relay 711</a></li></ul></span><p><br></p> 
   <br> 
   <br>
   <br>
</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-4">
			<div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField2_label" style='display:none'></div><div id="ctl00_ctl00_MainContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_PageContentPlaceHolder_RichHtmlField2__ControlWrapper_OregonRichHtmlField" class="ms-rtestate-field" style="display:inline" ><p><br><br></p></div>
